>>CPU server's are single user and don't accept connections.

a typing mistake there: ``terminal'' was meant, not ``CPU server''.
you can actually run aux/listen on a terminal, and even telnet in,
but only as the terminal's owner (or possibly `none').
its use is rather specialised!

